x4freetext: Last checking has been done.
C-12 was Used As Target. Other Information is Absent.
.Compound Nucleus Theory. Direct Interaction
Theory.
/by Authors/.Zero-Angle Corrections, Foil Thickness
Correction, Counting Loss Corrections were Represented.
/by Authors/.Cross Section For Proton Scattering from
Hydrogen in the Hydrocarbon Foils were Measured For at
Least Two Angles at Each Incident Beam Energy.Great
Care was not Taken with these Data, Because Further
Understanding of the P-P Interaction Requires Precision
Measurements Considered Outside the Province of this
Work.
Two Scintillation Detectors,the First Detector
Could View Protons Scattered at any Angles Between-
15 Degree and 170 Degree.The Second Detector was
Stationed at a Fixed Angle of -30 Degree to Monitor the
Strength Og the Elastically Scattered Beam.
A Virtually Drift-Free Double Proportional
Counter Proton-Range Spectrometer was Used For
Measurements of the Beam Energy.

x4freetext: All Recognized Errors in the Cross Sections
Have Been Analyzed and Reported in Two Separate
Categories.
"Associated" Errors are Those Largely Associated with a
Given Differential Cross Section, and May Distort the
Shape of a Distribution.  "Nonassociated" Errors are
Those Which Influence the Absolute Value of the  Entire
Angular Distribution.
The Associated Errors Quoted For Each Cross Section
Include Allowances For the Statistical Error in the
Number of Pulse Counted,the Estimated Error in the
Subtraction of the Background Continuum, the  Estimated
Error in the Counting-Loss Correction, the Estimated
Error in the Counting Time.
Nonassociated Errors Include Failure of the Current
Integration System, Lack of Knowledge of the Exact
Scattering Geometry, and Uncertainties in the Surface
Densities of the Scattering Foils.
The Estimated Standard Deviation of
Scattering Angle.
